initial_story: the aim of this paper is to provide a classification of multilingual andplurilingual electronic lexicographic resources which would enable, one the onehand, the implementation of quantitative and qualitative criteria to produce atypological taxonomy of lexicographical tools, such as dictionaries, as opposedto platforms and websites and, on the other, the distinction of multilingualand plurilingual resources in terms of their larger or lesser prototypingdegree. in addition to offering a thorough description of the differentresources, this paper also puts forward some parameters and typologicalproposals to define and demarcate a number of electronic resources,particularly multilingual dictionaries and portals, while also outlining, andeven questioning, the object of study of multilingual and plurilinguallexicography.
stories: This paper aims to categorize multilingual and plurilingual electronic dictionaries and platforms, enabling the development of quantitative and qualitative criteria for a typological classification of lexicographical tools. The classification will distinguish between resources based on their level of prototyping, and provide a detailed description of each type. Additionally, the paper proposes parameters and typological frameworks for defining and distinguishing electronic resources, particularly multilingual dictionaries and portals, while also exploring and questioning the scope of multilingual and plurilingual lexicography.

This study seeks to group multilingual and plurilingual electronic dictionaries and platforms, establishing a framework for evaluating and categorizing lexicographical tools based on their level of development and features. The classification system will identify and describe different types of resources, and propose parameters and frameworks for defining and distinguishing multilingual dictionaries, portals, and other electronic lexicographical resources, while also examining the boundaries of multilingual and plurilingual lexicography.

This research aims to categorize various electronic dictionaries and platforms that support multiple languages, creating a framework for assessing and organizing lexicographical tools according to their complexity and features. The classification system will identify and describe distinct types of resources, proposing criteria and frameworks for defining and distinguishing multilingual dictionaries, portals, and other electronic lexicographical resources, while also exploring the boundaries of multilingual and plurilingual lexicography.
